    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 111 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Representatives of the British Chiefs of
                        Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 880/6</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-30">30 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Size of Military Staffs for Terminal</hi>
                </p>
                <p>We communicated the views of the United States Chiefs of Staff regarding the size
                    of the military staffs for <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi> as set out in
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 880/3<note n="1" xml:id="d111fn1">
                        <ref target="#d107">Document No. 107</ref>.</note> to the British Chiefs of
                    Staff who replied saying that they agreed that large military staffs would not
                    be required at <hi rend="smallcaps">Terminal</hi>. The order of the staffs which
                    they have in mind to take is approximately as follows:— <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Each chief of staff will have with him, in addition to his personal
                            staff, four or five staff officers.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                        <item>In addition the secretariat will take with it enough personnel to
                            provide for the normal administrative running of the conference.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
